## 🎯 When to Use This Skill

### ✅ Use When

**User describes ANY system performance issues**:
- Performance: "慢"、"卡"、"lag"、"slow"、"sluggish"、"响应慢"
- CPU: "CPU 高"、"CPU 100%"、"风扇狂转"、"high CPU"
- Memory: "内存不足"、"memory"、"OOM"、"swap"
- Disk: "磁盘满"、"disk full"、"磁盘慢"、"I/O slow"
- General: "检查系统"、"健康检查"、"health check"、"系统诊断"

**Device types** (all supported):
- 🖥️ Servers: local server, remote server, cloud server (CVM), bare metal
- 💻 Personal computers: laptop, desktop, workstation, Mac, PC
- 🐳 Containers: Docker container, Kubernetes pod, LXC
- 📦 Virtual machines: VM, virtual machine, VPS, EC2, compute instance
- 🐧 All OS: Linux (Ubuntu/CentOS/Debian), macOS, Windows

**Execution contexts**:
- Direct execution: When user is on the problematic machine
- Remote execution: Combine with `remote-executor` skill for remote systems
  - Example: "Check CPU on 10.0.1.5" → Use remote-executor + standalone-checks

**Keywords that trigger this skill**:
```yaml
performance: [慢, 卡, lag, slow, sluggish, 响应慢, 延迟, latency]
cpu: [CPU, cpu, cpu高, cpu 100%, 风扇, fan, processor]
memory: [内存, memory, OOM, swap, 内存不足, RAM]
disk: [磁盘, disk, I/O, io, 存储, storage, drive]
health: [检查, 健康, health, check, status, 状态, diagnose, diagnostic]
errors: [错误, error, 异常, exception, 崩溃, crash, panic]
device_type: [server, computer, machine, laptop, desktop, VM, container, pod]
os_type: [Linux, Ubuntu, CentOS, macOS, Mac, Windows, PC]
```

### ❌ Do NOT Use When

- User wants **specific configuration changes** → Direct command execution or specialized skills
- Pure **software installation** queries → Package manager skills
- **Application-specific** issues (e.g., "MySQL won't start") → Use application-specific diagnostic skills first, fall back to this skill if suspected system resource issue
- User asks about **Windows servers** → Not yet supported

